cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA. 

The paper is about a reinforcement learning algorithm that uses eigenoptions to generate a diverse set of options for efficient exploration. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves hierarchical reinforcement learning, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a generalization of the algorithm to problems with continuous state-spaces, which is related to mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
